> Would help to know what year your bus is.  Pre-1960 buses do not have a
> M-code plate.  The ONLY way to check for proper VIN # is to find it
stamped on the
> body inside the engine compartment just forward and right of the rear
apron.
> While that one could be cut and welded in place, all other VIN #s can be
just
> unscrewed and replaced.
> Eric&Barb
